f=Brand Studio/pulse/marketplace/hook-writing/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "hook-writing" (revfactory/harness-100, 1.1k★ trusted repo board's okr-quality-checker). STATIC layer pulse's three-layer hook design: patterns their psychological mechanisms (curiosity gap, loss aversion, self-reference, narrative tension) stable human attention mechanics. TWO LAYERS LIVE ELSEWHERE, DESIGN: · tx=volatile platform executions dated, refreshable platform playbooks · tx=(social-content-calendar/assets/platform-playbook-template.md) · tx=ground truth hooks register (what actually worked audience, fed kai) · tx=register OUTRANKS patterns; patterns fill gaps flagged craft heuristics rule 0.6. FRAMING NOTE: source YouTube-framed (3-second decision, retention benchmarks, hook–thumbnail–title triangle). psychology transfers feed "first seconds" maps first line (X/LinkedIn), first frame (TikTok/Reels), cover+title (YouTube) per-platform mapping owned playbook's §3. retention benchmark table YouTube-specific illustration, cross-platform standard. HONESTY LAW: pattern #1/#12-style stats authority quotes TEMPLATES real numbers real sources only, system-wide no-fabrication rule. source's anti-clickbait rule (hook deliver promise) binding. --> · h1:Hook Writing YouTube Hook Specialist Guide=methodology designing hooks capture viewer within first 5–10 seconds. Extends scriptwriter agent's hook-crafting capabilities. · h2:The Psychology of Hooks=Viewers decide whether keep watching within average **3 seconds**. first-30-second retention rate exceeds 70%, probability algorithmic recommendation increases dramatically. **Core Principle**: hook create **Curiosity Gap** tension between what viewer "wants know" what they "don't know." · h3:1. Shocking Stat="87% people don't know about this" · h3:1. Shocking Stat=**How works**: Cognitive dissonance "Am one them?", **Best for**: Education, informational, health videos · h3:2. Contrarian Statement="Exercising much actually makes you gain weight" · h3:2. Contrarian Statement=**How works**: Challenges existing beliefs viewer wants see evidence, **Best for**: Science, lifestyle, business videos · h3:3. Result First="This method tripled monthly revenue. Let show you how" · h3:3. Result First=**How works**: Showing proof first builds trust methodology, **Best for**: Tutorials, testimonials, business videos · h3:4. Time Pressure="Do before watching video" · h3:4. Time Pressure=**How works**: Loss aversion fear missing out, **Best for**: Warnings, tips, news videos · h3:5. Story Opening="Three years ago, lost everything" · h3:5. Story Opening=**How works**: Narrative tension "What happened next?", **Best for**: Vlogs, documentaries, interview videos · h3:6. Provocative Question="Why rich people never buy this?" · h3:6. Provocative Question=**How works**: Self-reference effect "What about me?", **Best for**: Lifestyle, finance, psychology videos · h3:7. Before/After="[Before shot] [After shot] transformation took days" · h3:7. Before/After=**How works**: Visual proof provides instant persuasion, **Best for**: Transformation, review, DIY videos · h3:8. Challenge="If you watch video end, your coding skills level up" · h3:8. Challenge=**How works**: Gamification completion motivation, **Best for**: Education, skill-building videos · h3:9. Secret Reveal=secrets industry never tell you" · h3:9. Secret Reveal=**How works**: Desire resolve information asymmetry, **Best for**: Exposés, insider knowledge, expert videos · h3:10. Empathy Hook="Have you ever experienced this? [Specific situation description]" · h3:10. Empathy Hook=**How works**: Self-identification "This video me", **Best for**: Problem-solving, lifestyle videos · h3:11. List Teaser="I'll share things, important" · h3:11. List Teaser=**How works**: Curiosity structured anticipation, **Best for**: Listicles, ranking videos · h3:12. Authority Quote="Harvard researchers tracked years..." · h3:12. Authority Quote=**How works**: Trust transfer authority figure, **Best for**: Science, health, education videos · h3:13. Debate Starter="Is genius invention scam?" · h3:13. Debate Starter=**How works**: Polarized viewpoints desire confirm one's stance, **Best for**: Reviews, trends, debate videos · h3:14. Future Preview="In minutes, you'll able perfectly" · h3:14. Future Preview=**How works**: Explicit expected value return time investment confirmed, **Best for**: Tutorials, skill-building videos · h3:15. Mistake Warning="If you're making mistake, stop right now" · h3:15. Mistake Warning=**How works**: Loss aversion self-check, **Best for**: Tips, guides, warning videos · h2:Hook Combination Formula=`[Shocking Stat] + [Secret Reveal] \· → "A fact that 92% of people don't know: 3 secrets to making money" \·  \· [Result First] + [Time Pressure] \· → "This method grew my business 3x. Watch before this information goes away"` · h2:Hook Combination Formula=best hooks combine **2 patterns**: · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=hook's effectiveness maximized within **triangular structure**, isolation: · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=\| Element            \| Role                     \| Alignment Rule                                                   \| · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=\| ------------------ \| ------------------------ \| ---------------------------------------------------------------- \| · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=\| Thumbnail          \| Visual curiosity trigger \| Must match the hook's emotional tone                             \| · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=\| Title              \| Click driver             \| A keyword-optimized version of the hook's value promise          \| · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=\| Hook (first 5 sec) \| Watch-or-leave decision  \| Must immediately deliver/expand on the thumbnail + title promise \| · h2:Hook–Thumbnail–Title Triangle Alignment=**Prohibited**: hook ignores thumbnail/title promise, viewers perceive "clickbait" retention plummets. · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| Segment      \| Target Retention \| Drop-off Cause                            \| · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| ------------ \| ---------------- \| ----------------------------------------- \| · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| 0–5 sec      \| 90%+             \| No hook or excessive channel intro        \| · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| 5–30 sec     \| 75%+             \| Hook's value promise not delivered        \| · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| 30 sec–2 min \| 65%+             \| Insufficient density in the first segment \| · h2:Retention Rate Benchmarks=\| 2 min+       \| 50%+             \| No pattern interrupts                     \|